article.headline: E. Illinois 80, Anderson, Ind. 47
article.story: CHARLESTON, Ill. -- Jeremy Granger scored 18 points to lead Eastern Illinois to an 80-47 victory over Anderson, Ind., on Monday night. Granger also had seven assists and three steals. Alfonzo McKinnie scored 14 and L.C. Doss and Zavier Sanders had 12 each for Eastern Illinois (6-8). James Hollowell had 10 rebounds for the Panthers, who owned a 48-31 edge on the boards. Eastern Illinois led 41-32 at halftime and began the second half by outscoring Anderson 15-5, eventually building a lead that reached 36 points in the final two minutes. Brock Morrison led Anderson (7-4) with nine points. The Division III Ravens were just 17 of 55 from the field.
